Django Web-Based NVR Camera
Surveillance System Requirements
You are tasked with developing a modular web-based surveillance management system
using Django.‚Äã
The system manages and displays live camera streams from multiple Network Video
Recorders (NVRs) through their web preview interfaces.
Each NVR provides an HTTP/HTTPS web interface that shows cameras in a grid layout after
login.
Example NVR URLs include:
‚óè‚Äã http://61.246.225.154:8001/doc/page/preview.asp (Hikvision)
‚óè‚Äã http://136.232.171.218:20443/#/index/preview/ (CP Plus)
‚óè‚Äã http://182.237.17.227:8080/cgi-bin/main-cgi (Generic NVR)

Critical Technical Constraints
1. No RTSP Streaming
The system must NOT use RTSP streaming.
The user does not have RTSP URLs, so:
‚óè‚Äã Do NOT integrate VLC
‚óè‚Äã Do NOT use OpenCV streaming
‚óè‚Äã Do NOT use RTSP libraries
Instead:

Use Embedded Web Preview
The system must embed NVR preview pages directly using:

‚óè‚Äã HTML <iframe>
‚óè‚Äã or embedded browser panels
These preview pages already display live camera grids.

