3 Add NVR Page
Modal form for adding new NVR.

Fields
Location
URL/IP
Port (optional)
Username
Password

Example URL:

http://115.247.88.126:82/

URL Handling Logic
If URL contains port:
http://ip:82

Use that port.
If user enters port separately:
http://ip + :port

Connect Button
When user clicks Connect
System will:
1 Detect NVR type‚Äã
2 Login to NVR‚Äã
3 Fetch cameras‚Äã
4 Display camera list

NVR Brand Detection
Based on URL pattern.

Hikvision
/doc/page/preview.asp
/doc/page/login.asp

CP Plus
#/index/preview
port 20443

Generic
/cgi-bin/main-cgi

Adapter Pattern
Each NVR type has its own adapter.
Example structure:
class HikvisionAdapter:
def login()
def fetch_cameras()
def preview_url()
class CpPlusAdapter:
def login()
def fetch_cameras()
class GenericAdapter:
def login()
def fetch_cameras()

Login Implementation
Use Python requests session.
Example:
session = requests.Session()
session.post(login_url, data={
"username": user,

"password": password
})

Store cookies for preview access.

Camera Fetching
After login:
Load preview page.
Parse HTML using BeautifulSoup.
Extract:
camera name
camera id
preview path

Streaming Method
Grid loads preview using iframe.
Example:
<iframe
src="http://nvr-ip/doc/page/preview.asp"
width="100%"
height="100%">
</iframe>

Handling Special Cases
System must handle:

Password containing @
Use URL encoding.
admin:p%40ssword

Invalid URL
Return error.

Connection timeout
Show alert.

Invalid credentials
Show login failure.

Error Handling
Use try/except.
Display user-friendly alerts:
Connection failed
Invalid credentials
Invalid URL
NVR not supported

Application Startup
On server start:
1 Load NVRs from database‚Äã
2 Load cameras‚Äã
3 Display in sidebar

